id: pm-a22j
title: "Baseline agent token cost of the CLI surface: measure pm --help, per-command help, and contracts payload sizes before consolidation"
description: "Establish the before numbers the simplification epic is judged against: token/byte size of pm --help, sum of per-command --help, contracts --full, and MCP tool-list payloads, committed as a small measurement script + recorded snapshot. Duplicate check: no existing measurement/baseline item for surface size."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 1
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli",measurement,simplification
created_at: "2026-07-05T04:53:03.897Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-11T10:57:38.777Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: "Repeatable script reports byte+approx-token counts for pm --help, all command helps, contracts --full, and MCP tool list; baseline snapshot recorded in the item body/notes; script reusable for the after-comparison"
parent: pm-n7rr
risk: low
confidence: high
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-06T08:04:52.095Z",maintainer-agent,"Baseline evidence already measured by the 2026-07-05 external dogfood audit (record here so the chore starts from data): pm contracts --json 25,118 B; --availability-only 24,666 B; --action create 63,534 B; --full 520,414 B. Output-shape costs: pm list --limit 20 = 2,552 B TOON vs 3,773 B JSON (+48%); pm context = 4,582 vs 7,034 (+53%); trivial create echo 368 B vs 29 B --id-only (12.7x); tags = 43% of context brief output. Re-measure pm --help/per-command help on this workspace to complete the baseline, then re-run the full set after each pm-n7rr consolidation lands."
  "2026-07-11T10:57:38.776Z",maintainer-agent,"Help-surface census 2026-07-11 (completes the missing half of the baseline; contracts/output-shape numbers live in the prior note). Method (repeatable): extract command names from `pm --help`, run `pm <cmd> --help | wc -c` per command, tokens ~= bytes/4. Numbers on this workspace, current build:\n- Root `pm --help` = 9,423 B (~2.4k tok), 61 commands listed.\n- Sum of all 61 per-command helps = 164,643 B (~41k tok); full help surface ~= 174 KB ~= 43.5k tok.\n- Top offenders: update-many 11,218 / update 7,792 / create 7,494 / close-many 7,011 / package 6,204 / extension 6,077.\n- list-* family (list, list-all, list-draft, list-open, list-in-progress, list-blocked, list-closed, list-canceled) = 47,698 B across 8 commands = 29% of the per-command surface for what is ONE command with a --status flag: the single largest consolidation win for pm-n7rr.\n- Bootstrap path `pm contracts --summary` = 2,867 B TOON / 4,111 B JSON (vs contracts --full 520,414 B = 181x).\nRemaining for the AC: formalize as a checked-in script + measure the MCP tools/list payload; re-run the full set after each pm-n7rr consolidation lands."
body: ""
